mail-notification
------------------------------------------
Mail Notification is a status icon (aka tray icon) that
informs you if you have new mail.

It works with system trays implementing the freedesktop.org
System Tray Specification, such as the GNOME Panel
Notification Area, the Xfce Notification Area and the KDE
System Tray.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-11
  GConf2-2.22.0-1
  gdk-pixbuf2-2.12.9-1
  getlive
  glib2-2.16.3-1
  gmime2-2.2.20-1
  gnome-keyring-2.22.2-1
  gnome-vfs2-2.22.0-1
  gtk2-x11-2.12.9-1
  libX11_6-1.1.3-1
  libdbus-glib_1_2-0.74-1
  libdbus1_3-1.0.2-1
  libgetaddrinfo0-1.6.3-2
  libglade2-2.6.2-1
  libgnome2-2.22.0-1
  libgnomeui2-2.22.1-1
  libintl8-0.15-1
  libnotify-0.4.4-1
  libsasl2-2.1.19-3
  libxml2-2.6.32-1
  openssl-0.9.8g-1
  pango-1.20.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.11-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gettext-devel-0.15-1
  intltool-0.37.1-1
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.21-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://mailnotify.nongnu.org/

Canonical download:
  http://savannah.nongnu.org/download/mailnotify/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack mail-notification-5.4-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./mail-notification-5.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mail-notification-5.4-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/mail-notification-5.4-X.tar.bz2

